Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The landing page was desktop-only — at 390px viewport (iPhone 13/14),
the header overflowed (Sign In + Get Started button cut off screen),
the hero h1 at fontSize 72 forced one word per line, and section
headlines at fontSize 44/56 broke awkwardly.

Added a useIsMobile hook (window.innerWidth < 760) and applied it to:

- Header: J-only logo on mobile (no wordmark), hides Features/Pricing
  nav links + Get Started button (Sign In remains as the single CTA)
- Hero h1: 72px -> 38px, dropped the hard <br/> so text wraps naturally
- Hero p: 20px -> 16px
- Section paddings: 100/120/80px -> 48/56/72px on mobile
- Section h2 headlines: 44/56px -> 28/30px

Existing pricing/features grids already used auto-fit + minmax so they
stacked correctly — the fix is purely typographic + nav.
